---
/**
 * consensus-deep-dive · Figure 7 — crash quorum overlap (1 trustworthy node) vs
 * Byzantine quorum overlap (f+1, so ≥1 honest even if the liar is in it).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/distributed-systems/consensus-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Isolated as an .astro component because MDX's JSX
 * parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes. This
 * figure references no shared arrowhead markers, so it carries no <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 180"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Crash model: two majorities overlap in one trustworthy node. Byzantine model: the shared node might be the liar, so quorums must overlap in f+1 to contain an honest node."
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="150"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">CRASH · 2f+1 · quorum f+1</text
            >
            <circle cx="110" cy="80" r="46" fill="none" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-dasharray="4 3"
            ></circle>
            <circle cx="190" cy="80" r="46" fill="none" stroke="#1f3a5a" stroke-dasharray="4 3"
            ></circle>
            <circle cx="150" cy="80" r="11" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle>
            <text
                x="150"
                y="84"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">✓</text
            >
            <text x="150" y="142" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >overlap = 1 node, and it's correct</text
            >
            <text x="150" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >(crash nodes don't lie)</text
            >
            <line x1="300" y1="10" x2="300" y2="172" stroke="#d8d4c8" stroke-dasharray="4 4"></line>
            <text
                x="450"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">BYZANTINE · 3f+1 · quorum 2f+1</text
            >
            <circle cx="410" cy="80" r="50" fill="none" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-dasharray="4 3"
            ></circle>
            <circle cx="490" cy="80" r="50" fill="none" stroke="#1f3a5a" stroke-dasharray="4 3"
            ></circle>
            <circle cx="436" cy="80" r="9" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"></circle><text
                x="436"
                y="84"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                fill="#9a2417">✗</text
            >
            <circle cx="464" cy="80" r="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"></circle><text
                x="464"
                y="84"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                fill="#2f5d3a">✓</text
            >
            <text x="450" y="146" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >overlap ≥ f+1, so ≥ 1 of it is HONEST</text
            >
            <text x="450" y="160" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >even if the liar is in the intersection</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Under crash faults a one-node overlap suffices — that node is trustworthy. Under Byzantine
        faults the shared node might be the liar, so the overlap must contain <em
            >more honest than faulty</em
        > nodes → 2f+1 quorums out of 3f+1, intersecting in f+1.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
